stylometry: The factors and tradeoffs you must consider when deciding WHEN to place an order are where you are getting your supply from, the lead time, and the costs associated with these. You can either get your order from a supplier or manufacture the order yourself. When ordering from a supplier, there may be a greater lead time and you do not have much control of that. When manufacturing the order yourself, the lead time may be shorter but you may have more costs associated with it. You want to have a short lead time to make your customers happy, but you do not want to have a ton of costs to you.
